text: The Trump Admin’s climate denialism is actively harming our communities. These reports are supposed to help safeguard our communities against #ClimateChange – not be used as propaganda. #ClimateActionNow
Trump’s cruel and illegal #RemainInMexico policy is life-threatening for thousands of immigrants like Fernanda. This rule cannot stand. #DontLookAway
Crisis pregnancy centers lie and intimidate patients – they have NO BUSINESS receiving public funding. #MyBodyMyChoice

It was an honor to be inducted into the National #VotingRights Museum Women’s Hall of Fame! Civil rights leaders have fought for our right to vote for decades, but it's more important than ever that we keep working to ensure no one is blocked from the ballot box.

Alameda County has declared a public health emergency for the #Coronavirus to support ongoing response efforts. I encourage everyone to follow updates from @CDCgov and @CAPublicHealth for the latest news. Learn more from @CAPublicHealth on how to stay healthy

As we close out #BlackHistoryMonth, I’m deeply saddened by the passing of Dr. Raye Richardson. A trailblazer and an icon, she inspired, educated, and touched the lives of many. She was a dear friend and mentor. May her legacy live & may she Rest in Power. https://postnewsgroup.com/2020/02/27/dr-raye-gilbert-richardson-99-founder-of-marcus-books-oldest-remaining-black-owned-bookstore-in-america/

Let me be clear: this is no ‘peace deal.’ It leaves thousands of troops in Afghanistan with NO investments in peacebuilding, human-centered development, or governance reform. This is a step forward, but there’s still a long way to go to #StopEndlessWar.

We are continuing to fail low-income students. Everyone deserves a quality, affordable education – and some students are sacrificing a safe place to sleep to pursue their education. We need #DebtFreeCollege now!
Our continued quest for oil will do nothing but continue to devastate our planet, our ecosystems, and our endangered species. #ActOnClimate

It's appalling that people are using a public health crisis to justify blatant xenophobia. The best way to stop the spread of #coronavirus is to wash your hands, not push racist stereotypes. Go to http://www.cdc.gov for more resources.
Just a reminder that wage discrimination still exists in this country and that the average woman makes just 80 cents for every dollar a man makes. #EqualPay

2020 is the most important decade of our lifetime. If we don’t get serious about addressing and stopping #ClimateChange now, our children and grandchildren won’t have a planet to live on. #ActOnClimate
Everyone deserves to earn a living wage. #FightFor15 #RaiseTheWage

In the year #HR8 has stalled in the Senate, 2,887 children & teens died from gun violence. #EnoughIsEnough – it's past time for Mitch McConnell to do his job and bring this life-saving bill to a vote. #EndGunViolence #ForThePeople

The #Census2020 will begin on April 1 and this year we must ensure that the Black community is fully represented. When our community is undercounted, we lose out on critical federal funding for our neighborhoods. Encourage your family and friends to #BeCounted. #BlackCensus2020
As governor of Indiana, Pence ignored scientific evidence that led to an HIV outbreak – costing people their lives. Putting him in charge of the coronavirus response is beyond reckless.

Black children are expelled and suspended from preschool at 3 times the rate of white students. Yet DeVos refuses to provide Congress with the data we need to stop babies from being punished. How could anyone be proud of that? #TrumpBudget #ResignDeVos

I genuinely don't understand how Betsy DeVos can be proud of the #TrumpBudget. Her entire tenure has done nothing but hurt students of color, low-income students, and students with disabilities. She must be stopped.
Absolutely disgusting and despicable. How can we condone and excuse the murder of innocent people looking for a better life? #DontLookAway
Abortion is still legal in all 50 states – and we have to keep fighting to keep it that way. #MyBodyMyChoice
Children are freezing to death in refugee camps. We can't afford to delay – the US and the international community must come together to demand peace. #Syria

#Census2020 is so important for every American community because #WeCount. It will determine: School funding Roads, public transportation, & infrastructure #SNAP and Head Start funding Political representation …for the next years!
Last I checked, it’s hard to expand and “grow” a program when you’re cutting billions of dollars in funding and making it harder to cover people who need health care.

The Trump Administration is blowing up sacred Native American sites on public lands as part of its ineffective and xenophobic border wall. Trump’s cruelty won’t end until the administration ends. #NoBorderWall

From Charlottesville to El Paso, we are still being confronted with the same violent racism that took the life of Emmett Till. Today, with the passage of the #EmmettTill Antilynching Act, we send a strong message that we will not tolerate this bigotry. #OutlawLynching
Trump is deporting legal residents to places we KNOW they will face extreme persecution. Make no mistake: these xenophobic and white nationalist policies are putting lives in danger.

#DidYouKnow on this day in 1870, Hiram Rhodes Revels became the first Black U.S. Senator. During his time in office, he led key initiatives for racial equality and infrastructure development. #BlackHistoryMonth

Our criminal justice system is failing people with mental health problems. Instead of investing more money in new prisons and locking people up, we need to ensure that everyone has access to mental health care.

The #TrumpBudget wants to cut $5 billion from public education in 2021 alone. That's unacceptable. Public schools are the foundation of success for young people across the country, and every child deserves a quality education.

The Pentagon's culture of waste, fraud, and abuse of taxpayer funds has gone unchecked for years. It's past time to cut bloated and wasteful spending at the Pentagon and invest in diplomacy – not endless war. #AuditThePentagon

Just two weeks after the disastrous #TrumpBudget proposed slashing the CDC budget, Trump is now asking for coronavirus response funding. We need a coordinated & fully-funded response to this outbreak – not the last minute slap-dash Trump's requesting.

Only 3% of people in CA who qualified to clear their records of marijuana convictions received help after Prop 64 passed. We need more innovative ways to ensure restorative justice for communities impacted by the failed War on Drugs. #MarijuanaJustice
"All of the 10 current warmest years on record have occurred since 2004, and the past five years have been the hottest five." The time for debate is over. #ActOnClimate
PUBLIC CHARGE IS UNAMERICAN TRUMP JUST WANTS TO KEEP IMMIGRANTS OF COLOR OUT OF THE COUNTRY THIS IS XENOPHOBIA AND WHITE NATIONALISM #NoToPublicCharge

Katherine Johnson overcame racial & gender discrimination to work for NASA, playing a critical role in the U.S. space program. Her work inspired black girls to study STEM and fly into space. My prayers are with her family today. May she rest in peace.

B. Smith was a role model for millions of black women. She inspired so many to reach for the stars and fight for a cure for Alzheimer’s. It was a privilege to know her. My prayers are with her family and loved ones today. May she Rest In Power. #BSmith
We need urgent #ClimateActionNow – not cuts, slashes, and rollbacks to the programs we need the most. #TrumpBudget

So great to be back in the East Bay for my #BlackHistoryMonth town hall! It’s more important than ever that we engage, organize, and get counted to hold Trump accountable and fight to protect our civil rights.
TUNE IN: My February town hall on #BlackHistoryMonth, voting rights, and #2020Census starts now!

We've known for decades that there is no military solution in Afghanistan. Trump will be quick to claim an end to war but that requires a sustained, inclusive, and multilateral diplomatic effort. We also need to repeal the 2001 AUMF to #StopEndlessWar.
REMINDER: My #BlackHistoryMonth town hall is tonight! Make sure you swing by Beth Eden Baptist Church in Oakland to celebrate #BHM with us and discuss my ongoing work in DC #ForThePeople.

Is anyone surprised? Trump’s been doing Putin’s bidding in Washington since the moment he was elected – of course they’re going to do everything they can to keep him in office. Just more evidence Trump doesn’t care about our democracy or rule of law.

Are you celebrating #BlackHistoryMonth? Come to my town hall at Beth Eden Baptist Church in Oakland to celebrate #BHM and learn about @HouseDemocrats’ work to expand voting rights, ensure everyone gets counted, and fight #ForThePeople.
We should expect nothing less from a #LawlessPresident.

The new #SNAP rules proposed by the Trump Admin would kick thousands of children off their free school lunch programs. How can anyone defend taking food away from hungry children? We must stop this plan! #HandsOffSNAP
Trump’s cruel border policies violate basic human rights – full stop. No one should be forced to sleep in bathroom stalls or deprived of nutritious food. #DontLookAway

The conflict in Syria is one of the biggest humanitarian crises of the century. Hundreds of thousands of people are displaced, more are injured or dead. These horrific conditions must end. We must stand up to demand diplomacy and peace for the Syrians.

There is absolutely NO REASON for “tactical agents” to patrol our cities. The Trump Admin is transparently targeting sanctuary cities, traumatizing immigrant communities and playing games with public safety in the process. #DontLookAway

Make no mistake: Trump's cruel #SNAP cuts will hurt everyday families around the country. Our communities are counting on us to reject this immoral #TrumpBudget and stop this harmful rule from going into effect.

No one should have to travel 200+ miles to access comprehensive abortion care. These extreme bans and waiting periods just put people at risk and make healthcare inaccessible. #StopTheBans #MyBodyMyChoice
The lawlessness knows no limits. Make no mistake: Trump is a corrupt President, content to abuse the power of his office for personal gain – and now he’s normalizing it for other officials.

Just a reminder: Betsy DeVos has made it easier for for-profit schools to scam students, tried to slash funding for the Special Olympics, funneled millions to so-called “Education Freedom Scholarships,” and prioritized her rich friends over our students. She needs to go.

We’re on the verge of an #AIDS free generation – but we need to invest in programs we know work and increase access to care, especially for at-risk communities. If we truly want to #EndAIDS, we need to reject Trump’s harmful budget cuts. #TrumpBudget
Two years later, we still don’t know how many families are separated because of Trump’s inhumane policies. #DontLookAway
Let me be clear: Trump may be president, but he does not have free rein to do as he pleases. This is a democracy, not a dictatorship.

5 years ago today, my beautiful and brilliant mother, Mildred Parish Massey, left this earth and became an angel. My family and I miss her so much, but she will be forever in our hearts with love. Her spirit and legacy lives and we are grateful her love, sacrifices, & guidance.

While student loan debt is the highest its ever been – and growing – Trump is proposing devastating cuts to programs that offer student debt relief. Share if you agree we must make it easier to afford higher education, not harder. #TrumpBudget

Today is the beginning of National Engineers Week! Let's all commit to ensuring a diverse and well-educated future engineering workforce by increasing training, education, and funding for engineering careers. #STEMeducation
Trump's ineffective border wall not only wastes taxpayer funds, but also harms our border communities. This wall is a ridiculous use of our funds. #NoWall

The #TrumpBudget puts the wealthy ahead of everyday families by: Cutting Medicare, Medicaid Making it harder to afford college Exploding our national debt further by making the #GOPTaxScam permanent Cutting nutrition assistance
#DidYouKnow in 1992 Pearl Stewart became the first African American woman to edit a metropolitan daily newspaper when The Oakland Tribune named her Editor in Chief. #BHM

The #TrumpBudget isn't a war on poverty – it's a war on the poor. From his cruel nutrition assistance cuts to huge slashes to Medicaid, it's clear he doesn't can't about everyday families. #HandsOffSNAP

That’s why I introduced the Gun Records Restoration and Preservation Act with @SenatorMenendez today to allow the FBI and ATF to collect and maintain the data needed to properly investigate and prevent gun violence and make our communities safer.

February 14 marks two years since the deadliest high school shooting in US history. But the gun safety movement led by survivors is making an impact around the country. In honor of those we lost, we must continue fighting to keep our communities safe. #MSDStrong

.@HouseDemocrats are fighting to #ProtectTheDream – we passed #HR6, the Dream and Promise Act, to make sure that the doors of opportunity are open to all who know the US as their home. #HomeIsHere #ToImmigrantsWithLove
The time for “baby steps” is over. Climate change is the biggest threat facing our world this CENTURY. We need bold #ClimateActionNow!
#DidYouKnow Kwame Ture (also known as Stokely Carmichael) coined the phrase “Black Power.” He was a community organizer and founder of the Lowndes County Freedom Organization. #BHM

Trump is once again trampling on the separation of powers to fund his ineffective and xenophobic border wall. @HouseDemocrats have made it clear time and time again – we will not fund this vanity wall. #NoWall.

We can’t afford a reckless, unauthorized, and illegal war with Iran. I’m glad the Senate stood up to Trump’s warmongering and passed the War Powers Resolution – but we need to go further and repeal the 2001 & 2002 AUMFs to #StopEndlessWar!

The EPA has the biggest backlog of toxic waste cleanups in 15 years thanks to chronic underfunding from Trump – and now he wants to cut even more from their budget. These rollbacks are a huge threat to public health and the environment. #TrumpBudget

A vote for the #ERA is a long overdue vote for equality. I'm proud to support @RepSpeier's bill & @HouseDemocrats historic vote so that our Constitution better achieves the eternal promise of equal justice under the law! #ERANow

Trump continues his attacks on communities of color & the most vulnerable with his immoral budget cuts. His cuts to health care and Medicare – not to mention development assistance to so-called "s**thole" countries – all disproportionately hurt people of color.
Families across California and the country are feeling the effects of climate change every day. The longer we wait to act, the worse it will get. #ActOnClimate

Trump claims he’s “lifting” people off of food assistance – when in reality he’s kicking them off. The #TrumpBudget includes a $182 billion cut to SNAP, putting thousands of families at risk of going hungry. #HandsOffSNAP

Today I’m voting for #KeepItWild legislation to protect 1.3 million acres of #Wilderness. It’s an important #ActOnClimate measure, and it keeps our air and water clean. @HouseDemocrats are fighting the #ClimateCrisis and protecting our #PublicLands.

Actually, it’s very important for our national security – and the security of our brave servicemembers – that we not engage in an unauthorized and unconstitutional war. We need to #StopEndlessWar, pass the War Powers Resolution, and repeal the 2001 and 2002 AUMFs!

Trump wants to spend $2 BILLION on his useless border wall. Meanwhile, the #TrumpBudget proposes cuts to Medicaid, SNAP, & other critical programs that everyday families rely on to make ends meet. Trump doesn’t care about everyday families.

Trump's discriminatory #MuslimBan has not made us safer and goes against the fundamental principles of our Constitution. This country was built upon the ideals of equality and religious freedom. Trump’s attempts to bar these people based on their religion is un-American. #NoBAN

#OTD 111 years ago, the @NAACP was founded. Today, let’s recognize all the work they have done to advance political, educational, social, and economic equality for communities of color and reflect on the work yet to be done to reach racial equality. #BHM
Yet another politically motivated attack by Trump and Barr. California won’t back down from doing what’s right – #SanctuaryCities help #KeepFamiliesTogether and keep the public safe.
Asian American women get paid $0.90 to as low as $0.50 per dollar that white men make. The House has voted for equal pay. The Senate must do the same. #AAPIEqualPay #PaycheckFairness

Trump promised over & over again that he wouldn’t cut Social Security – but that was a lie. The #TrumpBudget cuts $24 BILLION from Social Security. This hurts our seniors, children, and families all across the nation. #TrumpLies
Trump is destroying our environment and natural treasures to help line the pockets of wealthy executives. We can’t let this stand. #MonumentsForAll
Trump is destroying 200-year-old cactuses, chopping them up like firewood. Yet, he touts his Trillion Trees Initiative. Unacceptable. #ClimateActionNow #NoWall
SNAP lifts millions of people out of poverty but the heartless #TrumpBudget cuts $182 billion from SNAP, putting thousands of families at risk of going hungry.
The Trump Administration is trying to demoralize the United States by destroying over 330,000 acres of protected and sacred land to build his xenophobic wall. He must be stopped. #NoWall #NoBan

Congratulations to the creators and cast of “Hair Love.” This film is a great example of the positive representation that we need to help normalize Black hair and raise attention to a bill I’m proud to co-sponsor: #CROWNAct.

Trump's immoral budget is full of reckless and cruel cuts to health care, education, housing, basic food assistance and more. All while funneling billions to a xenophobic boarder wall. Congress must and will reject it. #TrumpBudget
Trump’s efforts to kick 700,000 people off of food stamps is beyond cruel. We must fight to stop him. #HandsOffSNAP
The number of students experiencing homelessness is completely unacceptable – especially in the richest nation on Earth. We need bold action now.

Rep. Stark made a difference in the lives of millions of people across the country. His lasting influence on health policy reflects his deeply held values and courageous advocacy. May we carry his baton forward in our work for a more compassionate world, and may he rest in peace.

2 in 5 Americans can’t afford a $400 emergency. Too many are one medical bill away from financial ruin. We need livable wages and affordable housing to help families with the cost of living in America.

#DidYouKnow the first Black owned bank, The Savings Bank of the Grand Fountain United Order of True Reformers, was founded on March 2, 1889 by Reverend William Washington Browne, a formerly enslaved man. #BHM
The firing of Colonel Vindman was a clear and shameful act of retaliation. And not at all unexpected coming from Trump.
Where are the policies to reduce carbon emissions? Or fund the EPA? We must stop Trump’s assault on programs we know are working. #ClimateActionNow

This week we celebrated #BlackLivesMatterAtSchool week of action. I want to thank all of the amazing educators who work every day to make sure that our children know about #BHM – not just for a single month in the school year – because Black History is American History.

Today is National Black HIV/AIDS Awareness Day, and we’re in this together. We need to increase #HIV education, prevention, testing, and treatment among black communities. We all have a part to play in ending the cycle of stigma. #NBHAAD #StopHIVTogether http://www.cdc.gov/together

.@HouseDemocrats’ Puerto Rico earthquake supplemental includes significant funding to restart school operations, repair damaged road systems, address energy needs, & more. Our fellow Americans in Puerto Rico need our help, which is why I was proud to vote YES on today’s bill.

Our economy isn’t working for everyone, plain and simple. Wages are still too low, causing people to work two or three or FOUR jobs just to get by. We need to #RaiseTheWage so everyone has a fair shot.
People across the East Bay face gun violence everyday. They deserve to see McConnell finally bring up #HR8 for a vote so we can expand background checks and save lives. #EndGunViolence
While corporate profits are soaring, most Americans are working too hard for too little. The #PROAct strengthens workers’ power to organize and negotiate for a fair share of the profits they produce.
Trump's inhumane immigration policies are sending people to their deaths. Whatever happened to 'Give me your tired, your poor, your huddled masses yearning to breathe free?' #DontLookAway

The Voting Rights Act was passed over 50 years ago – yet communities of color still face extreme barriers when trying to vote. We need to channel our efforts to #RestoreTheVRA & protect access to the ballot box.

We can’t allow a two-tiered system where the wealthy have access to safe, #CleanWater while low-income families and communities of color are forced to drink contaminated water. We must stop these Trump rollbacks of our critical environmental protections!
A girl who undergoes female genital mutilation (FGM): - feels severe pain - experiences sexual dysfunction - faces higher risk of #HIV transmission FGM scars girls for life. It's time to #EndFGM.
Almost 13 million children live in poverty in the US. We know how to help #EndPoverty and help kids – we must invest in #SNAP and other critical assistance programs.

For too long, our #LGBTQ brothers and sisters have been criminalized for who they are and who they love. This justice is long overdue – but sadly remains out of reach for other members of the LGBTQ community.

This is a sad day for our country. After a sham trial with no witnesses or documents presented, Senate Republicans put party over country and acquitted the President. History will remember your actions. #DefendOurDemocracy
TRUMP IS LEADING THE LAWSUIT TO END PROTECTIONS FOR PRE-EXISTING CONDITIONS This man is incapable of telling the truth. #ProtectOurCare

No child should go to bed hungry in the richest nation on earth. And yet Trump is gutting #SNAP, pushing more children and families into poverty. This is a crisis and it must stop. We must fight to #ProtectKids and help everyday families thrive. #HandsOffSNAP
Trump’s speech last night was filled with nothing but hate-filled lies – not that we should be shocked when he’s told over 15,000 lies since he was elected. #TrumpLies
Trump is a national security threat who has shunned diplomacy at every turn and lead us to the brink of war with Iran – a war that Congress has not authorized. #StopEndlessWar #TrumpLies #SOTU
No human is illegal. #NoBan #NoWall #DontLookAway #SOTU

As Trump continues to chip away at reproductive rights, I'll keep fighting in Congress to ensure EVERYONE has access to comprehensive reproductive care. Abortion care is health care, and health care is a human right. #SOTU #MyBodyMyChoice
Glad Trump mentioned the HIV/AIDS crisis – let’s see what his budget does to back up his words. #EndTheEpidemic #SOTU

Trump isn't making health care more accessible. The only thing making a ‘comeback’ under this Administration is the number of people at risk of being pushed off their insurance. #TrumpLies #SOTU #ProtectOurCare

Since Day One, Trump has done everything possible to destroy protections for people with pre-existing conditions. He's ACTIVELY working to repeal the entire Affordable Care Act, threatening access to care for millions. #TrumpLies #SOTU

Trump's need to undo the Obama legacy is devastating our climate and environment. Regardless of what Trump says, #ClimateChange is real. The US needs to rejoin the #ParisAgreement and take #ClimateActionNow. #SOTU #TrumpLies
And more #TrumpLies!! His policies have done nothing to reduce Black unemployment – all he's doing is benefiting from the work done by the Obama Administration. #ThanksObama #SOTU

Don't listen to the #TrumpLies – he only cares about his billionaire buddies. His egregious #TaxScam just made his rich friends richer. @HouseDemocrats are working hard #ForThePeople to make sure the economy works for EVERYONE – not just the wealthy and well connected. #SOTU

From a sweeping #GagRule on #TitleX to restricting access to comprehensive reproductive health care, the Trump Administration wants to take away our rights at every turn. But we are here today to say no more! We will stand up & fight these harmful policies. #StateOfWomen

It's time for Trump to drop his cruel lawsuit to repeal the Affordable Care Act, which threatens access to care for millions of patients around the country. At tonight’s #SOTU tell Trump: Work #ForThePeople. #StateOfHealthcare

As we prepare for the 2020 census later this year, #DidYouKnow that communities of color are disproportionately under counted? This #BHM, let's fight for equal and accurate representation for our communities.

Don’t listen to Trump’s #SOTU lies tonight. Our economy isn’t working for everyday families. He's trying to rip health care away from millions. And we’re on the brink of war. While Trump is busy distracting from his dangerous agenda, @HouseDemocrats working #ForThePeople.

.@TheBlackCaucus is the conscience of the Congress, fighting for the soul of America when others have tried to shut us down. As Black truth-tellers and change-makers who have transformed this country, we must continue this work and redouble our efforts for justice. #CBC2020Summit
TUNE IN to #CBC2020Summit:
Happy birthday to my sister in Congress, @RepPressley! Your courage and leadership are inspiring, and I’m proud to call you my friend. #BlackGirlMagic

By refusing to #ActOnClimate, we are leaving our kids with a terrible burden. It's time to give everyone the facts on #ClimateChange and take action to stop it – before it's too late. #ClimateActionNow

Let me be clear: Congress has been missing in action for far too long. We have a constitutional responsibility to stand up and stop President Trump from starting an unauthorized and illegal war with Iran. It's past time to #StopEndlessWar.

Trump wants nothing more than to create a white nationalist haven in the US and ban everyone from "s**thole" countries. Make no mistake, @HouseDemocrats are hard at work to stop that from happening. #NoBan #ForThePeople

The House managers have made their case forcefully and eloquently: Trump is guilty of abuse of power and contempt of Congress. He betrayed his oath to the constitution, threatened our national security, and undermined our elections. He needs to be removed. #DefendOurDemocracy
This #BlackHistoryMonth, we honor the countless African Americans who fought for equality and civil rights, and the leaders of today who are carrying their torch.
We can’t continue business as usual – we need to take steps to stop and reverse #ClimateChange. Our children and our planet can’t wait. #ClimateActionNow
East Bay residents, today is the last day to enroll for health insurance for 2020! Visit @CoveredCA to enroll now. #GetCovered
Absolutely disgusting. Make no mistake – I’ll do everything I can to stop Trump’s xenophobic and white nationalist #MuslimBan. #NoBan
Trump’s reckless actions have brought us to the brink of war. It's past time for the Senate to repeal the 2002 AUMF to help reclaim Congress’s sole power to declare war so we can #StopEndlessWar!

Like so many towns across the US, my congressional district is home to #DACA recipients. As I fight to #ProtectTheDream in Congress, I hope all #DACA recipients in my community know that #HomeIsHere and keep their status up to date. Renew yours today

This is a cover-up, plain and simple. A fair trial needs witnesses, documents, and evidence – but Mitch McConnell and the GOP are going out of their way to prevent the public from hearing the truth. #DefendOurDemocracy

Trump is once again going after our health care – this time by attacking Medicaid. Capping funding is not flexibility – it’s taking away people’s coverage and access to care. We can't let Trump undermine the promise of quality, affordable health care.

Today, we celebrate #KorematsuDay and the contributions Oakland native Fred Korematsu made to fight the unjust internment of Japanese Americans during WWII. He challenged our government and our entire nation to stand against racial prejudice.

BREAKING: The House JUST PASSED my amendment to finally repeal the 2002 AUMF. It's more urgent than ever for Congress to do its job and prevent the President from using military force without Congressional authorization. #StopEndlessWar

The 2002 AUMF isn't needed for any current counterterrorism operations. PERIOD. This outdated and unnecessary AUMF has been on the books for far too long. It's past time for Congress to reclaim our constitutional authority on war and peace and #StopEndlessWar!
We can't let President Trump drag us into a war with Iran that Congress never intended to authorize – that's why we're voting today on my bill to repeal the 2002 Iraq AUMF. #StopEndlessWar

Make no mistake – allowing free-flowing pollution into rivers and streams would devastate natural habitats and threaten public health. We must increase protections for our environment and #ActOnClimate.

The #MovingForward plan will create almost 10 million jobs, by investing $760 billion in: -Modern Highways & Highway Safety -Passenger Rail -Airports -Clean Water and Wastewater infrastructure -Ports and Harbors -Brownfield Restoration -Broadband -And so much more #ForThePeople

#OTD 11 years ago, the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act was signed into law. Yet millions of women – especially women of color – still make much less than their male coworkers. We must fight to ensure ALL women earn #EqualPay and have the Senate pass the #PaycheckFairness Act!
We can't afford to put any more troops in harm's way for an unnecessary war of choice in the Middle East. It's past time to repeal the 2002 AUMF and #StopEndlessWar!

Our credit scores are our reputations. But credit reporting agencies often engage in unfair practices that keep consumers in the dark. Proud to support @RepPressley's the Comprehensive #CREDITAct to empower consumers and reform our deeply flawed credit reporting system.

Because of Trump’s dehumanizing #RemainInMexico policy, just .01% of asylum seekers are reaching safety. 1 year of Remain In Mexico is dangerous and deadly. This isn't normal – it's a systematic denial of human rights.
We need witnesses. We need documents. We need a fair trial. #DefendOurDemocracy

The 2002 AUMF never should have been on the books in the first place. Tomorrow, the House can come together in a bipartisan manner to pass my bill repealing this outdated and unnecessary authorization! #StopEndlessWar

Trump’s one-sided so-called “peace plan” is anything but. It green-lights annexation, goes against decades of bipartisan US foreign policy and international law, and conflicts with the principles laid out by Congress last year.
President Trump wants to kick hundreds of thousands off SNAP by imposing bureaucratic barriers between people who are going hungry and the help they need. #HandsOffSNAP
I’m presiding over the House Floor today as @HouseDemocrats continue our important work to #StopEndlessWar and say #NoWarWithIran. #ForThePeople

I'm closely monitoring developments about the coronavirus, and I'm glad @CDCgov will begin screening passengers at SFO for symptoms. The risk is still low for people in the East Bay, but you can follow these guidelines to help keep you and your loved ones healthy.

This just underscores the need for a fair and open trial in the Senate. The American people deserve to hear the full facts of the case – and that includes having witnesses testify and documents produced. #DefendOurDemocracy
No one should have to give up food to pay for prescription drugs. It’s time for the Senate to #LowerDrugCosts and pass HR 3!

This is a direct assault on our immigrant communities, betraying the core values of our country as a nation of immigrants. Make no mistake – we will keep fighting this bigoted and xenophobic rule. #NoToPublicCharge #ProtectFamilies

On the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz, let us take a moment to remember those whose lives were lost. In the face of rising anti-Semitism around the globe, we must stand together to declare #NeverAgain. #HolocaustMemorialDay

Three years ago, Trump issued his xenophobic and Islamophobic Muslim Travel Ban, undermining our values & Constitution. I have fought this discriminatory ban every step of the way and will keep working in Congress and the courts to demand #NoBan.

Trump’s #SNAP rule will have devastating effects on families across the country. Kicking people off of food assistance won’t help people find employment – it'll just make them hungrier while local governments struggle to meet increased need. #HandsOffSNAP
A fair trial has witnesses and documents – the Senate GOP is blocking both. The American people deserve the truth – and that starts with having John Bolton testify. #DefendOurDemocracy

I am heart broken upon hearing of the passing of Kobe Bryant, his daughter Gianna, and seven other passengers. Kobe was an inspirational leader, advocate, athlete and father. My condolences are with the Bryant Family and all those who lost a loved one.
I’ll keep saying this until everyone understands: ABORTION CARE IS HEALTH CARE, AND HEALTH CARE IS A HUMAN RIGHT. #StopTheBans

The blatant hypocrisy is outrageous. We all swore an oath to protect and defend the Constitution – it’s time that Mitch McConnell and the rest of the Senate GOP stood by their oath. #DefendOurDemocracy

Happy Lunar New Year! I hope that everyone is able to reflect on their accomplishments and celebrate this new beginning with their family and community. Wishing the East Bay and people around the world a healthy, peaceful, and prosperous Year of the Rat!

Pete Stark was a powerful voice for everyday families in the East Bay and around the country. His tireless work on health care & his fierce opposition to war helped make our country a better place. He will be missed.

By pulling out of international treaties and unilaterally attacking other countries, Trump is making our nation – and our world – less safe. It’s more important than ever that we prioritize diplomacy and peace.

Patients should not be prosecuted for accessing comprehensive reproductive healthcare. Everyone should have access to safe abortions. I remember the days of back-alley abortions and we will NOT go back! #StopTheBans.

Forced arbitration isn't alternative justice, but it is: Immunity from accountability Rigged by design, allowing the company to pick arbitrator Held in secret Forced arbitration signs away your constitutional rights. #FAIRAct gets it back

It makes no sense that 700,000 people living at the seat of government in DC don't have an equal voice in federal representation. DC residents deserve a vote in Congress, especially while paying federal taxes. It’s time for #DCstatehood.
It's past time for these racist polices restricting natural hairstyles to go. I’m excited to see these bills sweeping the country. #RespectMyCrown #CrownAct
These amazing students are leading the charge on #ClimateChange. They know now is the time to #ActOnClimate – and I'm proud to stand with them in support of teaching #ClimateChange in schools.

We’ve made incredible progress on HIV & AIDS, but LGBTQ people and folks of color continue to be disproportionately impacted. Read my op-ed in @eBARnews on why I will never stop fighting to tackle the HIV & AIDS epidemic.

Half a million kids who depend on free school lunch – sometimes as the only reliable meal in a day – could lose out if Trump's plan to gut SNAP goes into effect. We can't let Trump abandon our kids like this. #HandsOffSNAP
I’ll keep saying it until Trump and his war-hawk cronies understand: Trump does not have the Constitutional authority to strike Iran
I’m live with @RepDebDingell and student activists calling for climate change education in schools. #ClimateActionNow

I will fight tooth and nail against this administration's attempts to attack clean air and the public health. I stand with @RepDeSaulnier in rejecting the rollback of fuel economy standards. America deserves #HigherStandards

.@OIGatHHS found what we already know: Trump’s family separation policies are causing deeply harmful trauma for children. Today @appropsdems are working to shine a light on these horrible practices and hold this admin accountable #AppropriatorsatWork

It is past time to address gun violence as the public health crisis that it is! Today, @housedems are taking action #ForThePeople and holding a forum on the impact of gun violence on children and the need to pass universal background checks. #EndGunViolence

#HurricaneDorian2019 struck the Bahamas, leaving horrific devastation in its wake. I am proud to be introducing a resolution today supporting efforts to deliver urgently needed humanitarian assistance to victims of the deadly storm.

Today is National HIV & AIDS Aging Awareness Day. People living with HIV are living longer thanks to treatment. So let’s use today to call attention to the need to tackle aging-related challenges to HIV prevention, testing, treatment, and care. #HIVandAging

I am deeply honored by the nomination from @SpeakerPelosi to represent my Congressional colleagues at the @UN. I look forward to working with my colleagues in our engagement with the United Nations as we reaffirm our commitment to peace and security.
Trump is undoing decades of progress on environmental protection just to spite California. We will fight this for the sake of the health of our families and our communities.
No child in the richest nation on earth should live in poverty – but millions do. We owe it to our children to invest in their future. #InvestInKids

A trailblazer in every sense, Cokie Roberts paved the way for women in newsrooms and shone a light on stories long ignored. Her passing is a tragedy and I know her legacy will continue to inspire young women around the country. My condolences to her loved ones and friends.

Governor Newsom is right. If Trump is serious about addressing homelessness, he needs to quit the cuts to programs that keep people housed and invest in the things we know help families keep a roof over their heads.

Trump's #PublicCharge rule is rooted in racism. Millions will now be faced with the impossible choice of providing for the basic needs of their families or having a future in the U.S. #NoToPublicCharge

Over 500 women at public universities in California seek a medication abortion every month. They deserve equal access to comprehensive reproductive care. Proud that CA is leading the charge to expand the options for patients seeking abortions.
Our children know that climate change is real. It's amazing to see these brave young people turn their fears into activism – and I'll keep working in Congress to take #ClimateActionNow.

Receiving the #CBCFALC2019 Phoenix Award from my dear friend @GKButterfield was the honor of a lifetime! As we mark the 400th anniversary of enslaved Africans forced arrival to America, we must repair the damage from the past and keep our eyes focused on the future.
I stand with UAW as they fight for fair wages, affordable health care, and job security.

I’ll say it again – any strike against Iran would be completely unconstitutional. Trump doesn’t have the authority to unilaterally strike Iran. It’s time to end US complicity in the war in #Yemen. #NoWarWithIran

Hispanic Americans have contributed immeasurably to our country and the East Bay – as doctors, teachers, first responders, scientists, organizers, and entrepreneurs. Our diversity is our strength, and I thank you for all you do. Happy #HispanicHeritageMonth!

Mitch McConnell rushed the confirmation process to protect Kavanaugh, robbing the American people of a thorough investigation into the allegations. It’s never been clearer that he never should have been confirmed. #BelieveSurvivors
This rhetoric is literally life-threatening for women around the country. The anti-choice movement needs to stop spreading misinformation to push their agenda by purposefully misrepresenting facts.

#OTD 56 years ago, the lives of four young black girls were cut short in the 16th Street Baptist Church bombing. Today, let us honor their lives and memories and recommit ourselves to combating hatred and white supremacy in this country.

By refusing to #ActOnClimate, Trump and the Republicans are failing our children and threatening their safety. Greta is right – it's time to stop burying our heads in the sand and get serious about stopping #ClimateChange.

It's been 18 years since Congress passed the 2001 AUMF – and we've FINALLY started to debate #EndlessWar. Much progress has been made – a majority of members support my efforts to sunset the 2001 AUMF, but we have to be persistent until we repeal it for good. #StopEndlessWar

We’ve made great progress in the fight against HIV and AIDS, but African Americans and Hispanics continue to be disproportionately impacted. Thank you to everyone who joined us today for such an important conversation on tackling HIV and AIDS in communities of color. #CBCFALC2019

I was thrilled to welcome so many of my constituents to the Hill today for my annual Constituent Breakfast at #CBCFALC2019. You are doing the work back home to address the pressing issues facing African Americans. Thank you for joining us, and keep up the fight!
Always proud of our state for taking on this administration and doing what’s best for our environment and our communities. #DirtyWaterRule

Over 800,000 #Dreamers are protected by #DACA, but this administration has left the future of the program uncertain. I will continue to fight to #ProtecttheDream. But if your status expires before 2020, I urge you to renew it now.

Every day, at least 3 women in the U.S are murdered by their partners. #VAWA19 will save lives. Senator Mitch McConnell and Senate Republicans must stand with women and pass H.R. 1585 NOW! Survivors deserve nothing less. #VAWA4ALL
Military-grade weapons belong on the battle field -- not in our communities. It’s past time to renew the national #AssaultWeaponsBan to get these weapons of war off our streets once and for all.

We must reinvest in the black and brown communities hardest hit by the failed war on drugs while fighting for real restorative justice. Great discussion yesterday at #CBCFALC2019 about ensuring a diverse and more inclusive cannabis industry. #MarijuanaJustice

California is leading the way on tenant protections. As our communities deal with the affordable housing crisis, it's more important than ever that we make sure people aren't pushed out of their homes.

Yet another attempt by Trump to undermine Obama's legacy – this time, at the health and safety of our families. It’s time to stop padding corporate polluter profits and ensure our families have safe drinking water. #DirtyWaterRule
It’s time to hold Trump and his Administration accountable. No one is above the law.

Progress on HIV and AIDS for African Americans and Hispanics continues to lag far behind. As overall infection rates drop in the Bay Area, we must continue to work to address the health disparities impacting low-income people and communities of color.
Nearly 20 percent of residents in California live in poverty. We MUST do better. I will continue to fight hard to eradicate poverty and expand opportunity for all.
Gig workers deserve the same labor protections as anyone else. So proud that California is leading the way to make that a reality!

Republicans have tried to open Alaska’s Arctic National Wildlife Refuge to oil drilling for years. This week, @HouseDemocrats will vote to block them before it’s too late. This sacred landscape is no place for drilling. #ProtectTheArctic

Netanyahu must reverse course on his proposed annexation of the Jordan Valley and all Israeli settlements in the West Bank. This severely undermines a two-state solution and sustainable peace in the region.
Today we remember those we lost 18 years ago on 9/11 & the brave first responders who risked their lives to save others. #NeverForget

Institute for Policy Studies found that the average Black family would need 228 years to obtain the wealth of a White family. #400YearsLater, structural and institutional racism continues to permeate every aspect of American society.
African American homeownership is lower than when the Fair Housing Act was passed in 1968, but Trump wants to make it even harder. This has got to stop.

The House passed #HR8 in February. Universal background checks are supported by more than 90% of Americans, but Mitch McConnell refuses to hold a vote on this life-saving legislation. ENOUGH IS ENOUGH IS ENOUGH. It’s time for Congress to #DisarmHate.
The UN estimates that 40% of civil wars over the last 60 years were directly linked with environmental issues. Climate change is making the world less safe and we must address it now. #ActOnClimate

Hunger Awareness Month is personal to me. As a single mother, I relied on food stamps as a bridge over troubled waters. That’s why I’ve fought hard against the Trump Admin’s dangerous proposals to take away #SNAP from everyday families. #HandsOffSNAP
John Bolton never should have been National Security Advisor in the first place. His extreme policies have undermined our global leadership and national security. Good riddance.
Tonight I led a special order hour on the House Floor observing 400 years since the first slave ships arrived in Virginia. This began one of the darkest chapters in American history.

Doctors should be able to talk freely with their patients about all their options – not just what politicians deem acceptable. Trump's domestic gag rule will hurt patients across the country – we can't let it stand. #TitleX #NoGagRule

Receiving #SNAP makes it easier for families to qualify for other essential programs like Medicaid and free school lunch. This administration is trying to make it harder. It's time to invest in SNAP – for our kids, and for their future. #HandsOffSNAP
169 years ago today, California was formally admitted into the US as the 31st state. Happy #CaliforniaAdmissionDay to all who call the Golden State home!
Celebrating with beautiful people at the Oakland Pride festival today. Happy Pride, Oakland! Love who you want and love who you are. #LoveWins
How outrageous is our health care system that people are buying COUPONS for medical scans?! This is exactly why it’s time to pass #MedicareForAll and reign in our health care costs.
#SNAP has helped thousands of families put food on the table – but Trump is working behind the scenes to change who can get help. We need to expand access to SNAP now more than ever. #HandsOffSNAP

Once again, the presidential admin is imposing mean spirited actions that take us down the same road of isolation to Cuba that has failed for more than five decades. These actions hurt ordinary Cuban people and are wrong.

Healthcare costs are out of control – and we’re paying the price. More than 20% of people 25-45 took less than the recommended dose to make their medication last longer. It’s past time for the Senate to follow @HouseDemocrats’ lead and work #ForThePeople.

Travel can change your life and your perspective. Get ready for your next big trip by applying for your passport now! Turnaround times are quicker in the fall and winter. #BeginYourJourney http://travel.state.gov/passport

California's #CleanerCar standards have helped our communities breath cleaner air and save money at the pump. But Trump's rollback will throw that in reverse. It's time to get more aggressive in fighting climate change, not bury our heads in the sand.
Betsy DeVos is still failing our students – this time, by denying public servants the funds they were promised to pay off their student loans. It’s long past time for her to go. #DeVosResign
Families are struggling thanks to Trump's reckless policies. This jobs report is just another warning sign – it's time to fight #ForThePeople, not for special interests and GOP giveaways.

This admin's plan to expand oil drilling in the Bay Area would be devastating for our environment and for the Native American tribes that call the land here sacred. We don’t want fracking in Alameda County and I will fight this every step of the way.

Suicide is the second leading cause of death for people 15-34 in California. If you are struggling, don't be afraid to reach out – there are people who want to help. Call the National Suicide Prevention Lifeline at 1-800-273-8255. #SuicidePreventionMonth
Never shocking, but always disturbing to see how low Trump will sink to push his xenophobic agenda. Taking funds from school children is disgraceful.

Instead of actually helping everyday families make ends meet, Trump wants to unilaterally redefine who is poor in this country. We can’t let him get away with this. We must stop this mean spirited plan.

Like so many towns & cities across the US, the East Bay is home to #Dreamers. Even as the Trump Administration threatens their legal status, @HouseDemocrats are fighting to #ProtectTheDream. #Dreamers should still keep their status up to date.

Ending the federal prohibition on cannabis will help bring justice to communities all across the country. This is a promising time in the #MarijuanaJustice movement and I am proud of our forward movement in Congress, but it must be equitable for all.

The impact of this president’s reckless disregard for our environment will be felt long after he’s gone. We must continue to fight fiction with science, reject climate denial, and demand #ClimateActionNow.

The #DomesticGagRule would: -increase the number of unsafe abortions -increase maternal mortality rates -cause millions of patients to lose care Trump's policies are a direct threat to our health. We have to #ProtectX!
Our involvement in the suffering of millions of Yemenis is a moral outrage. Millions of people in Yemen are being bombed and starved, and Trump refuses to lift a finger to stop it.
A win for the people of Hong Kong who stood up to make their voices heard!

“One little boy, about 7 or 8, was separated from his father and did not know why... He believed that his dad was killed and he would also be killed.” The trauma this administration is causing is unimaginable. We must continue to fight this. #DontLookAway

Congress has the power of the purse – not the president. We refused to pay for his unnecessary border wall, so now he's stealing funds already marked for other purposes. This is illegal and an outrageous slap in the face to our men and women in uniform.
My thoughts and prayers are with the Bahamas as it begins the process of recovering from the devastation of Hurricane Dorian.
Trump's #DomesticGagRule is already forcing clinics to choose between critical health services and putting families across the country at risk. We must continue to fight to #ProtectX.

It’s not good enough to reconsider SOME #MedicalDeferredAction cases. We must continue to demand that this admin reverse this cruel policy in full so that immigrants like Maria Isabel Bueso can continue to get the care they desperately need. #SaveIsabel
Devastated by the news out of Santa Cruz Island this weekend. My heart goes out to all those who lost loved ones in this unimaginable tragedy.

September is #SickleCellAwarenessMonth. About 100,000 Americans are still living with the disease, and most are African American. It's more important than ever that we continue to raise awareness and fight this disease.

Overtime standards are out-of-date and leaving millions of workers behind. At a time when so many families are struggling to make ends meet, working people deserve to be paid for the hours they put in. That's why I co-sponsor the Restoring Overtime Pay Act. #FixOvertime #LaborDay

Without organized labor, we wouldn’t have: a minimum wage workplace safety protections overtime pay On #LaborDay (and every day!), we celebrate our union brothers and sisters in the struggle for economic justice. I stand with you in that fight. Happy Labor Day!

Lawsuits have blocked many of the abortion bans proposed around the country this year. That's what happens when we speak up, organize, and fight for what's right. We will continue fighting to #StopTheBans!

We grieve with Odessa and Midland and send condolences to the loved ones of those killed by gunfire. We pray for a speedy recovery for those injured. And we demand that Senator Mitch McConnell and the Senate act to pass gun safety legislation. This MUST end.

#OTD in 1964, LBJ signed the Food Stamp Act to ensure all families have the resources they need to keep food on the table. As a single mother, I relied on #SNAP as a bridge over troubled waters. I'll continue to fight to ensure all families have that same security. #HandsOffSNAP

Great news out of Sacramento that will make college more affordable for thousands of students! Californians owed $133 billion in student loan debt in 2018. This legislation is a major step toward correcting that.
Rooting for the @OaklandRootssc ahead of their debut game tomorrow! #KnowYourRoots

Hundreds of immigrants receiving life-saving treatment face deportation due to the Trump Admin’s cruel decision to end medical deferred action. One of them is the Bay Area’s Maria Isabel Buesos. We must fight this with everything we’ve got. #LetIsabelStay

-Average annual cost of college: $50,000 -Average household savings: $12,000 Our children deserve to get an education without sacrificing financial security in the process. Yet another reason it's so important to pass #DebtFreeCollege.

We’ve come a long way in the fight for #MarijuanaJustice, but there’s still more to be done. It’s past time to end our archaic federal prohibition on marijuana and do right by the communities of color devastated by the War on Drugs.

Thrilled to be Minneapolis today with @Ilhan, @RepPressley, and @SheliaJacksonTX18 for #CBCStateofBlackAmerica. From early childhood education to black maternal health and criminal justice reform, we’re tackling the important issues impacting our communities around the country.

Thurgood Marshall was an American icon. #OTD in 1967, he was confirmed as the first African American #SCOTUS Justice. We are forever a better country because of his passion for fairness and, justice for all Americans.

We should be helping state and local governments move towards cleaner energy and economy – not making it easier for big companies to pollute our planet. Trump's #Methane rule will hurt our communities, our health, and our environment.

This is a slap in the face to so many service members and diplomats serving our country abroad. This change serves absolutely no one. Trump has taken his xenophobia to new extremes. Outrageous.

Lookin’ good, Mr. Obama! One of the many moments we cherish from your time in office. #HappyTanSuitDay

Offering a pardon in exchange for breaking the law is a crime in itself – and it’s certainly not a joke. This is yet more evidence of this president’s lawlessness and another example of why I support opening an impeachment inquiry into this administration.

Medical decisions should be made by a doctor, not an ICE agent. Make no mistake, this new rule will hurt thousands of people across the country, all to promote Trump's xenophobic agenda. #DontLookAway

Absolutely shameful. Diverting money from FEMA to fund this administration’s cruel immigration policies is not just wrong – it’s unconscionably reckless at the top of hurricane season. I will fight this tooth and nail.

A critical win in the ongoing attacks against Roe v Wade. This Missouri law blatantly tried to take the right to abortion care away, and I am happy the court blocked it. We will not let up for one second to see access to abortion care denied to anyone.

The Amazon is burning. Our seas are rising. We’re facing a global climate crisis, and it’s outrageous that the president didn’t think this meeting was important enough for him to attend. #ClimateActionNow

We cannot trust this administration to set its own standards for the treatment of immigrant children. Proud that California is one of 19 states fighting back against Trump’s disgusting plan to imprison children indefinitely. #FloresDecision. #DontLookAway

Although far too little compared to the value of the lives lost and destroyed by the #opiodcrisis, there must be accountability for big pharma’s role – and drug companies need to pay for the damage they have done.
Congratulations to @UCBerkeley grad Adewale Adeyemo on his appointment as president of the Obama Foundation! Wishing him and the foundation much continued success.

What an awesome woman Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg is! She is a shining light of integrity, whose strength and commitment is an inspiration. Congrats to her on her honorary degree from the University of Buffalo. #NotoriousRBG
@HouseDems are hard at work delivering on our promises #ForThePeople. It’s past time for Mitch McConnell and Senate Republicans to take up our legislation.
.@wilmachan7 is right. It’s unacceptable that thousands of residents in Alameda County are food insecure. Glad you could join us to share your work to address this pressing issue in the East Bay.

Thank you @HilaryHoynes for joining us to share your research on how we can cut the child poverty rate in half in 10 years. Your work at the National Academy of Sciences has been critical to helping us chart a path forward.

Thank you @Ann_OLeary, Chief of Staff to @gavinnewsom, for being with us at our poverty summit, and thank you for your leadership on a budget that is bold and takes substantial steps to eradicate poverty.

Proud to be hosting this summit with Bay Area anti-poverty advocates on efforts to address childhood poverty. We now have substantive tools to cut our child poverty rate in half in 10 years and must have the political will to do it. Click here to watch.

99 years ago today, the 19th amendment moved us towards a fairer democracy, although women of color would not have full voting rights until 1965. Let us use today to continue the fight for equality and combat voter suppression that undermines our democracy. #WomensEqualityDay

The unfinished business of America is addressing the legacy of racism and the unique concerns of people of color, immigrants, women, LGBTQ Americans, and other marginalized groups. We've got to keep fighting for justice and equality for ALL - especially under this administration.

"No person is above the law. We have a system of checks and balances, and this president - this Trump administration - has totally eroded our system. And I think more members are beginning to see, what else is left?"

Today, our movement in Congress to repeal the Hyde Amendment has never been stronger. The #EACHWomanAct — which I, along with Congresswomen @janschakowsky and @RepDianaDeGette, reintroduced this year — now has 164 co-sponsors.
I am proud to stand with @RepDonBeyer in our letter to the FBI Director. @HouseDems will continue to stand up #ForThePeople to combat the growing threat of white supremacist extremist violence.

Today marks the International Day for the Remembrance of the Slave Trade and its Abolition. As we observe the 400th anniversary of the first Africans brought here to be enslaved, my support is stronger than ever for #HR40, the reparations commission study.
I voted against the 2001 AUMF because I knew then it was a blank check for endless war. It's long past time to reassert Congress’ constitutional authority and repeal the 2001 AUMF.

The Amazon produces 20% of the oxygen in the Earth's atmosphere. If we fail to combat climate change now, soon we won’t have clean air to breathe. We must take #ClimateActionNow. This is not a drill or a hoax.
This is an important milestone in establishing a civilian-led transitional government. I will continue my calls for accountability in support of the democratic aspirations of the Sudanese people

@AppropsDems are fighting these illegitimate efforts every step of the way. Foreign assistance funding strengthens our global leadership & our national security. We will stand up against efforts to undermine Congressional authority. #AppropriatorsAtWork

Today marks #BlackWomenEqualPay Day. We are more than halfway through the year, and today marks the day Black women’s pay finally catches up to what white, non-Hispanic men were paid in 2018. This fight for Black women is not over. I will keep up the fight for #EqualPayEqualWork
Politicians who reject basic science have no business making laws regarding our health. #StopTheBans

#FloresSettlement says children can’t be held in detention for more than 20 days. Now, Trump has decided to skirt that court settlement and imprison children indefinitely. This is disgusting and un-American. #DontLookAway #JusticeForOurChildren

More than half of all new #HIV infections in the United States are in the South and among black and Latinx people. We must address stigma head-on if we want to end the HIV epidemic in the United States.

It's been 175 days since @HouseDemocrats acted to end gun violence and passed #HR8 and #HR1112. We asked Mitch McConnell to hold a vote – and he hasn’t even responded. It’s past time for the Senate to expand background checks. #DoSomething #ForThePeople

We need to know if and when an election is compromised. The #SAFEAct will require post-election audits to help protect our national security. Mitch McConnell needs to stop holding up our bills and secure our elections #ForThePeople!
Use of lethal force as a last resort is now the legal standard for police shootings in California. Congratulations to all those who organized to get this over the finish line. #BlackLivesMatter
Congratulations Winnie Byanyima on being named the new head of @UNAIDS! Looking forward to working with you in our fight for an AIDS-free generation.
Tennessee wants a near-total ban on abortion. Extreme bans like this are nothing more than an attack on the constitutionally-protected right to abortion. #StopTheBans

Planned Parenthood provides critical health services to millions of low-income patients, and this will harm their health and the health of their communities. As Co-Chair of the @ProChoiceCaucus, I'll keep fighting against Trump’s continued attacks on #TitleX. #ProtectX
Finally, a small piece of justice for #EricGarner’s family. Long overdue. #BlackLivesMatter

#OTD 99 years ago, the 19th Amendment was ratified, granting white women the right to vote – but that right wouldn’t be extended to all women for another 45 years. We have to keep fighting to make sure EVERYONE has access to the ballot box.
The African American story is the American story. For centuries, African Americans have been fighting and struggling for those ideas we hold most dear — freedom and equality.
Hate speech leads to hate violence. #NotOneMore
Out of pocket health care costs have increased by 67% since 2008 -- while wages only rose 31%. Our health care system is broken, and it's time to fix it with #MedicareForAll!

It's outrageous that workers in the richest nation in the world don't receive paid sick days, parental leave, or make a living wage. Glad to see California pave the way for fair labor laws #ForThePeople!
It’s been one year without the Queen of Soul, #ArethaFranklin. Her voice inspired and empowered women, reminding the world that every woman deserves RESPECT. Rest in power.

From mothers trying to get prenatal care to critical peacekeeping missions, these cuts will have devastating consequences for people around the globe. I'll keep fighting against Trump's attempts to circumvent Congressional authority. #AppropriatorsAtWork
Never should have even been a question that children deserve access to food, showers, and sleep. #DontLookAway

More housing is good – but more affordable housing is better. As an appropriator, I’ll continue to fight for more federal funding to address the affordable housing crisis here in the Bay Area and around the country. #AppropriatorsAtWork
The last four Julys have been the hottest ever – and this July topped them all. Climate change is real and it’s not up for debate. #ActOnClimate
Happy birthday to my dear friend and sister in the struggle, @RepMaxineWaters! Thank you for your tireless work for justice and peace. Keep up the fight, and keep reclaiming your time!
Bans on abortion are: not based in science. harmful to women’s health. extremely unpopular. It's time to #StopTheBans!

Trump's domestic gag rule will significantly limit access to affordable birth control and reproductive health care for millions of women – especially women of color. The gag rule puts women's lives on the line & we can't let it stand. #NoGagRule #ProtectX

Like so many towns & cities across the US, the East Bay is home to 9,000 #Dreamers. They are our friends, neighbors, & colleagues and integral to our community. It’s time for Congress to Act and #ProtectTheDream. #DACA
Barring Congresswomen @Ilhan and @RepRashida from entering Israel sets a dangerous precedent and is outrageous. This move is motivated purely by politics and ideology.

My CBC colleagues and I have been fighting for the FBI to have more resources to address the actual domestic terrorism threat from white supremacy – not so-called "black identity extremists." This administration needs to get its priorities straight.
Around the country, temperature increases are already causing devastating and long-term consequences to the climate. It's time to #ActOnClimate before it's too late.

In another attempt to undermine the Obama legacy, Trump wants to deprive millions of everyday families of their much needed overtime pay. I’ll keep fighting #ForThePeople to make sure everyone gets the pay they earned.

Discrimination in the name of religion has no place in our country – let alone in the workplace. Make no mistake: Trump’s proposal is taxpayer-funded discrimination that targets women, people of color, and the LGBT community. We can't let it stand.

Only 10 of Texas’ 254 counties have a clinic offering abortion services – making it nearly impossible for patients to access their constitutionally-protected right to choose. We must keep fighting these extreme restrictions and #StopTheBans!

Yesterday the East Bay turned out to reject racism and stand up against gun violence. In moments of grief, it’s important to come together to speak truth, to heal, and to reaffirm our commitment to action #ForThePeople. Last night we did just that. #NotOneMore #DoSomething

Happy 84th anniversary to #SocialSecurity, which provides vital economic security for women of color. 37.8% of Black women and 36% of Latina women rely on Social Security for most of their income. Let’s protect them and work #ForThePeople. #SocSec84

Higher wages today mean more Social Security benefits tomorrow. Raising the minimum wage isn’t just good for American workers in the near-term – it also means greater financial security for our retirement savings. #RaiseTheWage #ForThePeople

There are 134 plants and 86 animals considered “endangered” in California under the #EndangeredSpeciesAct. Trump’s reckless changes to the law’s implementation are a direct threat to our ecosystem and environment.

We cannot accept a country where gun violence is expected. And we cannot accept a country where our leaders fuel the violence. Read my op-ed in the @EastBayExpress on why we must demand action from the Senate on gun safety.
Trump’s #PublicCharge rule would be devastating so many immigrant families here in California. Proud of our leaders in the Golden State for pushing back against this cruel proposal.
Climate change is already transforming how we live our lives. It’s beyond past time to act to address the global climate crisis. #ClimateActionNow
FACT: Trump directed McGahn to FIRE Robert Mueller. And then directed McGahn to LIE about it. That’s obstruction of justice. #RetweetTheReport
Fantastic news in the fight to address global health and equity. #Ebola

Join me at 5:30pm at Frank Ogawa Plaza for a community gathering in solidarity with all those impacted by gun violence around the country. It’s time to stand up against gun violence and speak out against white supremacy. #NotOneMore
The courageous people of #HongKong are fighting for democracy, freedom, and human rights. I stand with them in their fight to preserve democratic freedoms and the rule of law.

Patient health shouldn't be determined by a provider’s personal beliefs. Rolling back the Health Care Rights Law is a direct threat to people around the country – that's why I urged Sec. Azar to withdraw the proposed rule that would embolden discrimination. #PutPatientsFirst
From Day 1, this administration has made a mockery of our nation’s core principles and values, and so it continues... #PublicCharge
Our planet is under attack by this administration. Weakening the Endangered Species Act so developers can profit more from the destruction of our environment is reckless and shameful.
Wishing a happy first day to all the East Bay students heading back to school and good luck to the parents who are juggling it all!
